Abstract:  the Production Cross Sections and
Longitudinal-Momentum Distribution of Very Neutron-Rich
Isotopes have Been Investigated in the Fragmentation of
A 950 a MeV 197-Au Beam in the Berillium Target.
Seven New Isotopes (193-RE, 194RE, 191-W,192-W, 189-TA,
187-HF AND 188-HF) And the Five-Proton-Removel Channel
Were Observed For the First Time.  The Reaction
Mechanism Leading to the Formation of these Very
Neutron-Rich Isotopes is Explained in Terms of the Cold
Fragmentation Process.  An Analytical Model  Describing
This Reaction Mechanism is Presented.

x4codes.hlp: GSI Helmholtzzent. f. Schwerionenforschung, Darmstadt, Germany

x4freetext: The Error is Given in Authors` Table.
The Uncertainties of Included Corrections were
Estimated to be of the Order of 20%, and Together with
The Statistical Error They Determine the Final Accuracy
Of the Measured Cross Sections.
Abrasion-Ablation Model.
To Describe the Production of Extremely Neutron-Rich
Nuclei by Cold Fragmentation, an Analytucal Formulation
Is Presented.
Longitudinal-Momentum Distributions.
The Primary Beam Intensity was Recorded
Permanently by Measuring the Current Induced in a
Secondary-Electron Transmission Monitor.
Two 5 mm Thick Scintillation Detectors Which
Which Measured the Horizontal Positions at the Center
And at the Exit of the Spectrometer As Well As the
Time-Of-Flight in the Second Half of the Separator.
Multiple-Sampling Ionisation Chamber was Mounted
At the Exit in Order to Determine the Energy Loss of
The Reaction Products.
Data Table was Received from Web Site of Gsi.
The Data were Rounded by Compiler.
But Datum For Re-194 Production is Absent in the
Table. Therefore the Datum has Been Read from Figure.
An Attempt to Receive 194-Re Datum from J.Benlliure was
Not Successful. No Reply from J.Benlliure.
